race.comment: WESTBOUND (16) couldn't quicken with the leaders off a sedate tempo last start, finishing 1.6L away at his first time over the mile. The draw is a query, but he drops a half kilo and CJP remains in the saddle. Looks to have plenty of upside and can return to winning ways. SKYTALKER (6) jumped the $1.60 favourite first-up at Bunbury and got the cash there in rather easy fashion. The wide draw is a niggle, though he looks ready to take the next step now and he'll take beating if he can improve on the fresh performance. MAXWHOOSHTAPIN (3) was a little disappointing over 1800m last time out and coming back to the mile looks a good move now. He has the early speed to offset the sticky gate and the 3kg claim comes in handy. Can play a leading role. AUDIO BOY (8) missed in a photo here as favourite last time out and has claims on that effort. KELORA (9) hasn't been far away recently and can be in the finish once again.
